        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): reset custom trigger sessions safely",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- emit reset hooks for matched custom resetTriggers like `!new` / `!reset` instead of only slash commands\n- rotate generated/default reset transcripts to the new session id while preserving only validated explicit `sessionFile` paths\n- add regressions for Discord bang reset triggers and unsafe outside transcript metadata\n\nFixes #55474.\nSupersedes #56362.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nDiscord/custom reset trigger aliases such as `!fresh` could rotate a session without running the expected reset hook fallback path, leaving custom reset sessions inconsistent with the built-in `/new` and `/reset` behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Rebased onto current `origin/main` and resolved the conflict in `src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.ts` by preserving both the current session-prepared callback path and the custom reset-trigger fallback hook mapping.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.reset-hooks-fallback.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 123 tests on commit `5fff06e3e642121b7d5d3c95768108f2cb31f8c0`.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.reset-hooks-fallback.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.test-fixtures.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.ts` passed.\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` passed.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.reset-hooks-fallback.test.ts src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-models.test.ts src/config/sessions/sessions.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n",
